This incredibly cute game puts kids in charge of their own musical productionâchoosing dancers, costumes, and techno tracks, and choreographing moves using simple swipes and taps. Once the performance starts, the real fun begins: you can fling items at the stage, set off pyrotechnics and other cool effects, and even cheer (or boo) your squad. Seeing the payoffâan awesome video you can shareâwill encourage players to jump right back in and start working on their next great show.

Nothing beats a kid-friendly game that keeps the whole family captivatedâand Toca has us snipping, straightening, and styling to our heart's content. Once we've perfected our customer's silly new âdos, we make sure to add some accessories, snap a pic, and share the hair.

editorialNotes.standard: See the beauty and power of ABCs in an app where every letter holds secret words. Touch an F, and it sprouts a foot, then feathers, then a fan; a G becomes a guitar in a garden with ghosts. Kids will love poking and prodding their way to the end of the alphabet, while parents will dig the unpredictability and gorgeous animation in this Apple Design Award winner.
editorialNotes.short: Interactive alphabet learning where words and letters come to life.

editorialNotes.standard: Ready to unleash your cartoon alter ego? CHOMP takes your face and sticks it on dozens of interactive animations, letting you instantly record the bizarre and hilarious results. Scenarios can turn you into a wacky superhero, a concert pianist, a pandaâeven water dripping from a tap. The beautiful, simple, feel-good illustrations make for the type of silly fun that guarantees laughter from all ages.

editorialNotes.standard: Once again, the creators of The Human Body and Simple Machines have turned playtime into a rich learning experience. Tinybopâs sandbox-style app lets kids experiment to their heartsâ contentâseeing what happens when they move the sun, whip up winds, and cause rainstorms. A zoomed-out view illustrates the broader water cycle at work, while fascinating closeups show things like the effects of changing temperatures and strengthening tornadoes on everyday life. We also dig the detailed study guide offering extra info and discussion ideas.
